title: For Sale:  SAFE act registration and how to beat it.
postcontent:
Found this on a different forum.  Great idea:

April 15, 2013 is the day NY State Police are supposed to make the "assault rifle" registration form available.

This link has a preliminary draft of the form:
http://www.thetruthaboutguns.com/201...stration-form/

The form can be mailed or filled out online and submitted electronically. You will receive a verification either by mail or email once they've processed your registration.

It's expected that there will be little if any compliance from gun owners.

So I was thinking that instead of using non-compliance to show my contempt for the law, perhaps over-compliance will be more effective.

I thought I'd mail in a couple bogus registrations a week until the one year registration period is over. If every gun owner did the same thing, we could literally overwhelm the database and backlog any verification/disqualification for years.

The preliminary form asks for name, dob, address, last four numbers of your social security number, and your NYS driver license number. I was thinking I'd put "non-applicable" in the driver license number box and make up everything else. Maybe pull some names from the obituaries and police blotter. I figured I'd use apartment buildings as the address for most of my bogus registrations, since its much less likely that the post office will get a return to sender notice from an apartment complex as opposed to a single family home.

Even if they get a return to sender notice, or an application with no driver license number, they are going to have to enter it and do their due diligence to "keep us safe." I mean, if someone registers a full auto Ma Deuce, or a felon has submitted a registration form, they are going to have to check that out no matter what. Think of it, a couple million fictitious registrations and all the police man hours spent trying to track these illegal guns and their owners down. Gun owners could render the whole thing useless.

I also thought it might be a good idea to fill out a legitimate registration form, photocopy it, burn the original, and put the copy with your guns so you could always claim you mailed one in, just in case.

On second thought, maybe we shouldn't do that. That would be wrong...

The Package:

PSL-54C Rifle with less than 100 rds through it Excellent condition Bolt hold open on last shot

5-10 rd magazines, in pouch with cleaning rod, brushes etc. and dual compartment oiler

1000+ rds of 7N1 Premium Soviet Sniper Ammo (2 unopened 440 rd tins and 160 in paper wrap)

200 rds surplus ammo 

Extra Buttstock for mounting of cheek piece

The 7N1 Soviet Sniper Ammo, is more rare than the rifle, It has only been imported a couple of times and probably never will be again, it is the "Holy Grail" of this caliber.  it was designed specifically for the Dragunov SVD, TIGR, and the PSL it is match grade, FMJ.  Bullet designed with hollow cavity and lead "knocker" to destabilize after impact causing bullet to yaw. On GunBroker it goes for $1/rd

title: For Sale:  MICRO SLICK your gun parts!
postcontent:
Cerakote™ Micro Slick is a dry-film lubricant that is able to withstand high temperatures and extreme pressures. The Micro Slick coating is able to lubricate, resist wear, and also act as an anti-seize agent while preventing galvanic corrosion or bonding of the metals.  Micro Slick is virtually unaffected by temperatures ranging between 800 and 1200 degrees Fahrenheit  When two adjoining surfaces are coated with Micro Slick it prevents surface-to-surface contact, which reduces friction and wear between the two surfaces. An example of this would be to coat a bolt carrier group on an AR 15 and the inside of the upper receiver. This combination would reduce the amount of friction between the parts and help the firearm to function more smoothly.

Micro Slick is generally applied, but not limited, to internal, moving parts such as engine parts, bolts, bolt carrier groups, trigger groups, rails, etc. This product comes in a dark grey color only. Micro Slick your trailer hitch ball and never have to grease it again! Micro Slick your axe head and it will glide through the wood more smoothly and won't get stuck in any sap! Micro Slick your bicycle chain and gears for a smoother ride with little to no dirt and grime build up on your chain and eliminate having to oil your chain!
